 Despatch - Despatch police are asking for the public's help with identifying a pedestrian that was hit by a train in Despatch on Saturday morning. "On Saturday, at around 7:30am, police were summnoned to an accident scene involving a train and a pedestrian in Holland Street, Despatch," said police spokesperson, Sergeant Majola Nkohli. "At scene, police found a lifeless body of a man approximately in his late twenties, wearing a black jacket, a pair of blue jeans and a pair of green sneakers. "It is said that the unknown man was walking on the railway lines when he was hit by a passenger train that was travelling from Uitenhage towards Port Elizabeth. "Police are urging anyone, who could assist in identifying the deceased to contact the Despatch police at 041 933 8831." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 